The edit reflects the accurate description of the studies cited, where they mention that the opinion that Yasin Burushaski is the "pure" or "original" is widely held by people from Yasin. This attitude is not specific to the people of Yasin, and speakers of each region consider their dialect to be "good" or "original" [Backstrom & Radloff (1992)]. The original article stated "the pure Burushaski is spoken in Yasin Valley" as a fact despite no such indications in the cited article.
